{
  "text": "Higher azimuthal modes can be obtained similarly as\u03a8 which is defined by D \u00b1 m \u2261 e \u2212i(m\u00b11)\u03c6 (\u01eb \u00b1 \u00b7 \u2207) e im\u03c6 , where \u01eb + = \u01eb, and \u01eb \u2212 = \u01eb * is the complex conjugate of \u01eb. The calculation of (A 3) is algebraically complicated but can be done by the computer algebra system Mathematica [CITATION_1] , which requires considerable computer resources and practically can be carried out only for m \u2264 5. But this suffices to deduce the general solution (3.4).",
